result.description:
processes (Month 4)
Results of this task will be presented in a written report that presents the materials and the manufacturing processes selected as the most suitable for the application.  More specifically, the document will present:
•	A literature review to show that a viable composite axle does not already exist for rail vehicles and composite shafts being used in other sectors;
•	Extraction of the appropriate standards which can be related to the expected service conditions: fatigue/impact, FST and environmental conditions;
•	Collection of data from the literature in relation to those conditions;
•	A listing of the pros/cons of different manuf9acturing techniques based upon the selected materials;
•	A concept design of low to mid fidelity that incorporates the materials and manufacturing techniques.
